This program can be used to read and write data as text, binary, and objects.  It is an eclipse project, and best viewed there.

The only arguments are the flags defined below.  Data is hard-coded into the main class, and can be changed to test different data.

To run, call the application from the command line using the arguments below, or use a run configuration in eclipse.

Usage:
--help - show these instructions
--text - read and write a file using text format
--binary - read and write a file using binary format
--object - read and write a file as an object stream